---
---

<section
  data-test="comparison-section"
  id="comparison"
  class="py-24 px-4"
>
  <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold mb-4">Spec vs. No spec</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--text-secondary)] text-lg max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        See the difference a structured spec makes to your AI-assisted development workflow.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <!-- Before panel -->
      <div
        data-test="panel-before"
        class="p-8 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-500/5"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-red-500/20 flex items-center justify-center text-red-400 font-bold">✕</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-red-400">Without RootSpec</h3>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">"Build me a dashboard" — AI guesses the scope, features, and design</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Requirements exist only in chat history. Nothing is machine-readable.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Tests are optional afterthoughts. Coverage is unknown.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Regenerating the same feature gives a different result every time.</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-red-400 mt-0.5 shrink-0">—</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">No audit trail. Impossible to know what was built vs. specified.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <!-- After panel -->
      <div
        data-test="panel-after"
        class="p-8 rounded-xl border border-brand-primary/30 bg-brand-primary/5"
      >
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
          <div class="w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-brand-primary/20 flex items-center justify-center text-brand-primary font-bold">✓</div>
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-brand-primary">With RootSpec</h3>
        </div>
        <ul class="space-y-4">
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-brand-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0">+</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Five-level spec: philosophy → truths → interactions → systems → user stories</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-brand-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0">+</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Every requirement is a YAML user story with acceptance criteria and DSL tests</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-brand-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0">+</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Tests are generated from the spec and run automatically by the impl agent</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-brand-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0">+</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Deterministic output: same spec → same feature, every time</span>
          </li>
          <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
            <span class="text-brand-primary mt-0.5 shrink-0">+</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--text-secondary)]">Full compliance report: X/Y stories passing, linked to spec lines</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
